reviews.review_text: sounds great this recording really takes me back it sounds great i really liked this show it had a smoothness about it great night

One of the best days of my life! The best all around show that I saw in a two week stretch from Sandstone in Kansas to Foxboro MA.  I didn't appreciate the set-list at the time, but looking at it now, wow! I remember vividly the bright music coming from Gerry and the boys! Brent's key's were magic! Gerry's sound on Standing on the Moon was enveloping as the full moon rose over the stadium.  Just wished it was a little darker. The 30 minutes from Standing to the He's gone jam was the best 30 minutes of music I ever experienced live!
Excellent Sound Quality That is the exact mix of the show speakers sounds great!!! The peak of The Grateful Dead on Brent's last tour.

The Best Dead! I’ve been to many Dead shows 1988-1994 and this is the best one I got to witness! Someone reviewing mentioned the Sandstone show on the 4th (good God it was hot that day) and caught the Indy shows too that tour (all were great but Louisville stole the show so to speak)

RIP Brent a few weeks later :-(

#TheCircusIsInTown
#PlayGloria!
